              "asynchronous_ai_overview": false,
              "markdown": "To unfreeze an iPhone, perform a **force restart** , which safely reboots the device without erasing your data.[](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cTtHbP7X82c) [[1]](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cTtHbP7X82c)[[2]](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4rel9lOwAII&t=9)\n\nFor most modern iPhones (iPhone 8 and newer):\n\n1. Press and quickly release the **Volume Up** button.\n2. Press and quickly release the **Volume Down** button.\n3. Press and hold the **Side (Power) button** until the screen goes black and the Apple logo appears (usually takes 10\u201315 seconds), then release the button.[](https://support.apple.com/guide/iphone/force-restart-iphone-iph8903c3ee6/ios) [[1]](https://support.apple.com/guide/iphone/force-restart-iphone-iph8903c3ee6/ios)[[2]](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cTtHbP7X82c)[[3]](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hla7j5ZVHU4)[[4]](https://www.youtube.com/shorts/h6j6IRElxmQ)[[5]](https://www.youtube.com/shorts/Smx0AXXojiI)\n\nFor a clear visual guide on exactly how fast you need to press the buttons to get your phone to restart:![Related video thumbnail](https://api.dataforseo.com/cdn/i/07210055-2120-0139-0000-7974ab7c9a1a:4)\n1:59[How To Force Restart iPhone 52K views \u00a0\u00b7\u00a010 months ago![](https://api.dataforseo.com/cdn/i/07210055-2120-0139-0000-7974ab7c9a1a:5)\nYouTube\u00a0\u00b7\u00a0Technomentary](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oHKYYbaXaAU) \n\nIf your specific model is older, the process varies slightly:\n\n- **iPhone 7:** Press and hold the **Volume Down** and **Sleep/Wake** buttons together until the Apple logo appears.\n- **Older models with a Home button:** Press and hold the **Home** and **Sleep/Wake** buttons simultaneously until the Apple logo appears.[](https://www.cnet.com/tech/mobile/unresponsive-iphone-how-to-force-restart-or-reset-your-device/) [[1]](https://www.cnet.com/tech/mobile/unresponsive-iphone-how-to-force-restart-or-reset-your-device/)\n\nIf your phone still won't respond, charge it for at least 30 to 60 minutes and try again. For more detailed troubleshooting, check out the [Apple Support Guide](https://support.apple.com/guide/iphone/force-restart-iphone-iph8903c3ee6/ios).[[1]](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/discussions/windowsinsiderprogram/my-iphone-screen-frozen-how-can-i-unfreeze-an-unresponsive-iphone/4513252)[[2]](https://support.apple.com/guide/iphone/force-restart-iphone-iph8903c3ee6/ios)",
